</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="58.[163,1070,808,889]" pageId="58" pageNumber="1203">
E t y m o l o g y: The specific epithet, 
<emphasis box="[572,684,808,829]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="1203">trituberosa</emphasis>
, is a Latin compound name that stems from the prefix 
<emphasis box="[331,363,839,860]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="1203">tri-</emphasis>
(= three) and the noun 
<emphasis box="[620,673,838,859]" italics="true" pageId="58" pageNumber="1203">tuber</emphasis>
(= swelling). With reference to the 3 tumescenses on the pronotal disc.
</paragraph>
